Description: Clipboard history popup for GNOME (Super+Ctrl+V)
 A resident GTK daemon that remembers what you copy and pops it up on
 Super+Ctrl+V, like the Windows clipboard history. Arrows pick an entry,
 Enter pastes it into the active window. Keeps both text and images and
 matches the Yaru theme. Works on X11 and Wayland. History is kept in
 memory only (no disk, no sync) — it does clipboard history and nothing
 else.

